<subSubSection id="D1946509FA7CD42FFF2B5987AF5AFF7D" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF2B5987AEEDFF44" blockId="10.[166,702,175,202]" box="[166,702,175,202]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="C27981EEFA7CD42FFF2B5987AEEDFF44" box="[166,702,175,202]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA7CD42FFF2B5987AE62FF44" authority="(Loew, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[166,561,175,202]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7CD42FFF2B5987ADC2FF44" bold="true" box="[166,401,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Ophiomyia simplex</emphasis>
(Loew, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 57–60)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF5659F5AF5AFF7D" blockId="10.[219,777,221,244]" box="[219,777,221,244]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
M a t e r i a l e x a m i n e d. Stara Pokrovka, 
<date id="ED301042FA7CD42FFDFF59F5AE88FF7D" box="[626,731,221,243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" value="2010-06-13">13.06.2010</date>
, 2 ♂.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1946509FA7CD42FFF56583DAF81FD21" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF56583DA89AFE00" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
R e d e s c r i p t i o n. Head (fig. 57, 58). Orbit strongly projected above eye in profile, shining; 2 orb s, 3 fr s; frorb sta reclinate, sparse; keel and vibrissa lacking; lunule with round deepening in centre; ocellar triangle conspicuously shining, reaching the level of 2nd orb s; maximal height of eye 5.0 
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7CD42FFD97585DAE78FE01" bold="true" box="[538,555,373,399]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">×</emphasis>
maximal height of gena; 1st flagellomere small, rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF5658BCAEB5FE41" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
Wing. Costa ending after R 
<subScript id="050A34C7FA7CD42FFD96588FAE65FE3B" attach="left" box="[539,566,423,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">4+5</subScript>
; last and penultimate sections of M equal; calypter grey, fringe and margin black. Length of wing 2.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF5658FDAEA1FE60" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" box="[219,754,468,495]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Mesonotum black; 2 dc; halter and legs black.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF5658DCAE8AFDA0" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
Male genitalia (fig. 59, 60). Distiphallus 0.11 mm long, 2.0 
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7CD42FFC1758DDAFF8FD81" bold="true" box="[922,939,501,527]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">×</emphasis>
as wide as endophallus (ventral view). Basiphallus highly asymmetrical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF565B1DAEA8FDE1" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Occurring in most of Western Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7CD42FFC0D5B1CAFB3FDC0" box="[896,992,564,590]" name="Ukraine" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA7CD42FFC625B1CA8DCFDC1" author="Guglya, Yu. A." box="[1007,1167,564,591]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" refId="ref13136" refString="Guglya, Yu. A. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 1. 28 new species for the fauna of Ukraine // The Kharkiv Entomological Society Gazette. - 2011. - 19 (2). - P. 61 - 66. - Russian: Gugлi Ю. A. Izuciнii фauны мiнiрuющik мusik podсiмiйсtva Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) Ukрaiны. Сoobщiнii 1. 28 нovыk vidov dлi фauны Ukрaiны." type="book" year="2011">Guglya, 2011</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7CD42FFF2B5B7CAD10FDE1" box="[166,323,596,623]" name="United States of America" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">United States</collectingCountry>
and Eastern 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7CD42FFE515B7CAE65FDE0" box="[476,566,596,622]" name="Canada" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Canada</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA7CD42FFDC85B7DAEBCFDE1" author="Spencer, K. A. The" box="[581,751,596,623]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" refId="ref13567" refString="Spencer, K. A. The Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark - Klampenborg: Scandinavian Sci. Press, 1976. - Part 1. - 304 p." type="book" year="1976">Spencer, 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF565B5DAFAAFD01" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" box="[219,1017,628,655]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
H o s t p l a n t. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA7CD42FFE1C5B5DAE79FD01" authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[401,554,629,655]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asparagaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA7CD42FFDBB5B5DAF48FD00" box="[566,795,628,655]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Asparagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinalis">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7CD42FFDBB5B5DAF48FD00" box="[566,795,628,655]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Asparagus officinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA7CD42FFCC85B5DAFBEFD01" author="Spencer, K. A." box="[837,1005,628,655]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" refId="ref13600" refString="Spencer, K. A. Host specialization in the world Agromyzidae (Diptera) - Dordrecht: Kluwer Acad. Publ., 1990. - 444 p. - (Ser. Entomologica. Vol. 45)." type="book" year="1990">Spencer, 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7CD42FFF565BBDAF81FD21" blockId="10.[166,1225,276,687]" box="[219,978,660,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
B i o n o m i c s. Larva forms external stem mines (
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA7CD42FFC965BBDAF96FD21" author="Spencer, K. A." box="[795,965,660,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" refId="ref13600" refString="Spencer, K. A. Host specialization in the world Agromyzidae (Diptera) - Dordrecht: Kluwer Acad. Publ., 1990. - 444 p. - (Ser. Entomologica. Vol. 45)." type="book" year="1990">Spencer, 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
